properties.otherAdvice:
The Everest Carnival - Epsom Day at Royal Randwick Racecourse from 12:25pm.

Traffic may be heavier on roads around the racecourse including Anzac Pde, Doncaster Ave, High St, Alison Rd and Darley Rd.

Special event clearway parking restrictions will be in effect on sections of Ascot St from 8am to 7pm and High St from 3pm to 7pm.

Clearways are strict no-parking zones, and apply even for local residents and RMS Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Check signs carefully as vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies.

arrangementElements.html:
Special event clearways are strict no-parking zones, and apply even for local residents and RMS Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Check signs carefully as vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies. If your vehicle is towed call 132 701 to find its new location.

RANDWICK 

FROM 8AM TO 7PM

  • Ascot St between Doncaster Ave and the roundabout at the racecourse (both sides)

FROM 3PM TO 7PM

  • High St between the gate 2 entry to UNSW and Anzac Pde (southern side)

properties.headline: NRL - Sunday 4 October - SYDNEY OLYMPIC PARK M4 Mwy, Homebush Bay Dr, Parramatta Rd approaching ANZ Stadium
properties.publicTransport: Route 525 and 526 buses will be diverting around closures in Sydney Olympic Park. Visit transportnsw.info to plan your trip.
properties.otherAdvice:
NRL Finals: Rabbitohs v Knights at ANZ Stadium from 4:05pm to approx 5:50pm.

Traffic may be heavier than usual roads approaching ANZ Stadium including the M4 Mwy, Homebush Bay Dr, Concord Rd, Lane Cove Rd, Parramatta Rd, Centenary Dr and Silverwater Rd

Road closures will also be in place from 11am Sunday 4 October until 6am Monday 5 October on sections of Olympic Blvd, Showground Rd, Murray Rose Ave and Dawn Fraser Ave. 

Motorists should allow extra travel time if driving in the area.

arrangementElements.html:

  • Murray Rose Ave between Showground Road and Park Street
  • Dawn Fraser Ave between Olympic Boulevard and Park Street

properties.headline: NRL - Friday 2 October - PENRITH Mulgoa Rd, Jamison Rd at Panthers Stadium
properties.publicTransport: Visit transportnsw.info to plan your trip.
properties.otherAdvice:
NRL Finals: Panthers v Roosters at Panthers Stadium from 7.50pm to 9.50pm approx.

Traffic may be heavier than usual on Mulgoa Rd, Jamison Rd and Jane St/Great Western Hwy through Penrith as fans travel to the game during Friday evening peak.

Fans should allow extra time as parking is limited in the area and will be in high demand.
